    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6079f4c8-8741-4ed9-9efb-5507fdfb93fa\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. prepare 2 empty files `a` and `b`\n2. run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua a b`\n3. add text to file `a`\n4. switch to buffer `b` via `:bn`\n5. `:wa` (the autocmd does not trigger‚ùå, but the `modified` option of buffer `a` has changed)\n6. `:bn` (the autocmd only triggers when switching back to `a`)\n\nminimal.lua:\n\n```\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\n\t\"BufModifiedSet\",\n\t{\n\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\tprint(os.date())\n\t\tend,\n\t}\n)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe autocmd should be triggered at step 5\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1948+gc53e00889d\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim does not support `BufModifiedSet`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.13.5-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.8.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnightly",
